SIMPLE: luciferian
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Luciferian
<hw>Lu`ci*fe"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of
or pertaining to Lucifer; having the pride of Lucifer; satanic;
devilish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the Luciferians or their
leader.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Luciferian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Luciferian
<hw>Lu`ci*fe"ri*an</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld> <def>One
of the followers of Lucifer, bishop of Cagliari, in the fourth century,
who separated from the orthodox churches because they would not go as
far as he did in opposing the Arians.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Luciferin</ent>⟦br⟧
